  "texts": [
    "Let j = 0,..., ⌊n/2⌋ -1, the jth output bit of the Von Neumann extractor is then given byVon Neumann(x) j = x 2j if x 2j ̸ = x 2j+1 ∅ otherwise, (43)where the empty set ∅ denotes that there is no output bit in that round.",
    "Note that, contrary to the other constructions, the output length of the Von Neumann extractor is probabilistic.",
    "For example, a valid input X is one that is IID with an unknown bias p i = p for all i.",
    "In this case, the approximate (due to finite sampling from X) output length is given bym ≈ p(1 -p)n, (44)which gives an entropy loss k -m of (1 + (1 -p)p/ log 2 (max{p, 1 -p}))k 1 ≥ 3k 1 /10 i.e.",
    "implying at least 30% entropy loss."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}